# Pre-Deploy Quality Gate

**No deploy, push, or production release until the full test journey passes.**

## Mandatory command

From `fleetflow---car-rental-&-finance-dashboard/`:

```bash
npm run test:all
```

This runs (in order, stops on first failure):

1. Calculations — `test-calculations.mjs`
2. Sample data — `test-sample-data.mjs`
3. Filters / pagination — `test-entry-filters.mjs`
4. Integration — `test-integration.mjs`
5. Fleet / multi-car — `test-fleet.mjs`
6. Oil change — `test-oil-change.mjs`
7. Production build — `vite build`

Exit code must be `0`. Message `All tests passed + build OK` must appear.

## Before deploy, also verify

- [ ] `npm run test:all` passed in this session (agent must run it, not assume).
- [ ] No secrets in commits (`.env`, credentials).
- [ ] DB migrations (`db:migrate`, `db:init`) tested if schema changed.
- [ ] Deploy scripts (`deploy/`, `db:push`, `users:push`) only run after tests pass (see `deploy-quality-gate.mdc`).

## If tests fail

1. Fix application or test code — do not skip steps in `test-all.mjs`.
2. Re-run `npm run test:all` until green.
3. Only then proceed with `build`, `db:push`, server restart, or hosting deploy.

## Agent workflow summary

```
Change code → update test scripts → npm run test:<area> → npm run test:all → deploy
```

Treat a failed quality gate as a **blocker**; do not suggest deploy workarounds.
